  "output": "Verification done — 11/12 confirmed live, 1 stale. Full report below.\n\n## N+1 Query Patterns\n\n**1. `signedOpeningBalance` called per-account in loops** — 2 sites\n`AccountTreeCache.swift:58-67` and `ReportRepository+FinancialStatements.swift:196` (balanceSheet). Each ledger/account triggers separate SQL when no override row exists. `trialBalance`/`profitAndLoss` already batch `movementTotals` — same fix needed here.\n\n```swift\n// current — one query per account\nlet balances = ledgers.map { ledger in\n    try reportRepository.signedOpeningBalance(for: ledger, filter: filter, openingContext: openingContext)\n}\n\n// fix — batch query, single IN(...) or GROUP BY, map results back\nlet balances = try reportRepository.signedOpeningBalances(for: ledgers, filter: filter, openingContext: openingContext)\n// implementation: one SELECT with account_id IN (...), GROUP BY account_id\n```\n\n**2. `VoucherService.loadAccounts` — one SELECT per account** (`VoucherService.swift:1164-1175`)\n```swift\n// current\nfor id in ids { try accountRepo.findById(id) }\n// fix\ntry accountRepo.findByIds(ids) // single WHERE id IN (...)\n```\n\n**3. `BankReconciliationService.reconcile` — O(n·m) match loop** (`BankReconciliationService.swift:96-119`)\n```swift\n// current\nfor s in statement { vouchers.first(where: ...) }\n// fix — index vouchers once by amount+date bucket, O(n+m)\nlet byKey = Dictionary(grouping: vouchers, by: matchKey)\nfor s in statement { byKey[matchKey(s)]?.first }\n```\n\n## Caching Opportunities\n\n**4. GSTService — no caching, new instance per call** (`GSTView.swift:190,201,208`, `InvoicePDFService.swift:39`)\n```swift\n// current — recreated + recomputed every reload/export/PDF\nlet svc = GSTService(db: db, companyId: companyId)\n\n// fix — cache computed summary keyed by (companyId, period, changeToken), same pattern ReportCache already uses\n```\n\n**5. `ReportService` — only 4/10 report types cached** (`ReportService.swift:8, 36-113`)\n`gstSummary`, `dayBook`, `outstanding`, `stockValuation`, `cashFlow`, `stockAgeing` bypass `ReportCache` entirely (lines 81-109). Wire same cache wrapper used for `trialBalance`/`balanceSheet`.\n\n**6. `changeToken()` runs COUNT/MAX query on every cache lookup** (`ReportService.swift:164`, called from `:138`)\n```swift\n// current — cache.value() always re-verifies with a query\nfunc value() { let token = changeToken(); ... }\n\n// fix — debounce changeToken check (e.g. only re-verify every N seconds or on explicit invalidate signal), don't hit DB per read\n```\n\n**7. Cache invalidation too coarse** (`VoucherService.swift` — 8 call sites: 96,108,199,399,512,578,704,774)\nEvery voucher op wipes **all** cached reports company-wide (`ReportService.swift:158-162`). Scope to affected accounts/date range instead.\n\nNote: `AccountTreeCache` invalidation flagged in prior audit as blocking UI — checked again, that's fixed already. `markAccountTreeDirty()` wired on all post/edit/reverse paths, `reload()` runs on `Task.detached` in 500-row chunks, off main thread. No action needed there.\n\n## Redundant Computations\n\n**8. `AccountPicker` — sort+filter recomputed on every keystroke** (`AccountPicker.swift:147-170`)\n```swift\n// current — plain computed properties, full re-sort+filter every access\nvar sortedAccounts: [Account] { accounts.sorted { ... } }\nvar filteredAccounts: [Account] { sortedAccounts.filter { ... } }\n\n// fix — cache sortedAccounts once (invalidate on accounts change only), filter cheaply off the cached sorted list\n@State private var cachedSorted: [Account] = []\n// recompute cachedSorted only in .onChange(of: accounts), filter from it per query\n```\n\n**9. `InventoryService` — full movement replay per insertion** (`InventoryService.swift:455-483`)\nEvery stock-out pulls entire chronological history and reruns `InventoryValuationEngine().replay()`, then issues one `updateMovementTotalValue` call per movement.\n```swift\n// fix — running-balance carry: persist last valuation state, replay only movements after insertion point, not full history\n```\n\n## Memory Leaks\n\n**10. 17 of 19 `Task {}` closures capture `self` strongly, no `[weak self]`**\nOnly `KeyboardBridge.swift:32` and `AppEnvironment.swift:299` guard. Representative sites: `CompanyPickerView.swift:50`, `GSTView.swift:134`, `VouchersView.swift:165`, `VoucherEditViewModel.swift:273` (autosave, long-lived), `BackupSheet.swift:41`.\n\nRisk mostly low for short-lived one-shot tasks, real for `VoucherEditViewModel.autosaveTask` (long-lived, re-scheduled). Fix that one first:\n```swift\nautosaveTask = Task { [weak self] in\n    try? await Task.sleep(...)\n    guard let self else { return }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n## Batch-Insert Naming Bug\n\n**11. `insertBatch` methods loop individual INSERTs, not real batching**\n`LedgerLineRepository.swift:23-44`, `VoucherItemLineRepository.swift:20-`\n```swift\n// current\nfor line in lines { try db.execute(\"INSERT INTO ...\") }\n// fix — multi-row INSERT or wrap loop in single db.write transaction (currently not even transaction-wrapped per prior audit note)\n```\n\n---\n\nPriority order: #5/#6 (report cache gaps + changeToken cost) and #4 (GSTService) hit every screen load — biggest win for effort. #1/#2 hit every balance sheet render. #11 is correctness-adjacent (no transaction = partial-write risk on crash), fix before it bites in prod.\n\nSay which one to fix first, I'll do it.\n",
